Test set contains 95 test cases with the arrays of sizes 100 to 1000 (step 50). For each size test set contains 5 different test cases.

This test set is used to show the differences between fast (n log n) and slow (n^2) algorithms. In the Quick info tab above it is clearly seen that the BubbleSort and the Insertion sort algorithms tend to be slow while the QuickSort and the JavaSort are fast.
